  "prompt": "How can you troubleshoot an iPhone that won't sync to iTunes?",
  "response": "Here are several steps to troubleshoot an iPhone that won't sync to iTunes:\n\n1. Basic Checks\n- Ensure you have the latest version of iTunes installed\n- Use a different USB cable\n- Try a different USB port\n- Restart your computer and iPhone\n\n2. Connection Issues\n- Check that your iPhone is unlocked\n- Verify the USB connection is secure\n- Remove and reconnect the cable\n- Trust the computer if prompted on your iPhone\n\n3. Software Solutions\n- Update iTunes to the latest version\n- Update iOS on your iPhone\n- Restart iTunes\n- Restart your computer\n- Reset iTunes sync settings\n\n4. Advanced Troubleshooting\n- Check for conflicting software\n- Disable antivirus temporarily\n- Reset iPhone network settings\n- Try another computer\n- Check for hardware issues with the cable or port\n\n5. Recovery Methods\n- Use Recovery Mode\n- Use iTunes' \"Restore\" or \"Update\" options\n- Try third-party syncing software\n- Reset iPhone to factory settings (last resort)\n\n6. Additional Checks\n- Ensure sufficient computer storage\n- Check for any iTunes error messages\n- Verify Apple ID and iCloud settings\n\nIf problems persist, contact Apple Support for professional assistance.",
